# Knowledge map — {{ project_name }}

A router, not a corpus. It tells you the single file to open for a task. Open
that file and nothing else.

## Read-first order

1. `.claude/constitution.md`
2. `.claude/policies/00-index.md`
3. this map
4. `PROJECT_BRIEF.md`

## Task type to consult

_Plugin skills auto-invoke by description; to call one explicitly use `/psotobverse-utils:<name>`._

| Task type                       | Consult                                                       |
|---------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| Orientation / where do I start  | `PROJECT_BRIEF.md`, then this map                             |
| Design a risky change           | run `/deliberate`                                             |
| Audit coherence across the repo | run `/reconcile`                                              |
| Directed execution toward a goal| run `/goal`                                                   |
| Messy repo / rebuild the index  | run `/index` or `/tidy`                                       |
| Record a decision               | `docs/adr/`                                                   |
| Where do outputs go             | `outputs/OUTPUT_LAYOUT.md` + `.claude/policy/paths.allow.json`|
| A recurring lesson              | `learning/PLAYBOOK.md`                                        |
| Prior material / source corpus  | `context/`                                                    |
